Git Hub :

1.	Create an account
2.	Create new repository 
3.	Open command prompt, go to the project folder which needs to be pushed to git.
   	i.e. C:\Users\rajas\eclipse-workspace\Udemy-maven-demo
4.	git init	-	initialize git
5.	git status	-	shows folders which are not checked in (red color)
6.	git add .
7.	git status	-	shows folders which are checked in (green color)
8.	git commit -m "First git commit"
9.	git push origin master, but before that open Git Bash
10. ssh-keygen
11.	git push origin master, will ask Git ssh key and pushes the code